Classes in com.cornell.opencomm.jingleimpl used by com.cornell.opencomm.jingleimpl
BaseElementType
          This is the base class to represent all elements as defined by XEP-0166, XEP-0167, XEP-0177 This contains utility functions needed by classes that represent each xml element.
CandidateElementType
          This Class encapsulates a Candidate Element as described in XEP-0166 (Jingle), XEP-0176 (ICE UDP) and XEP-0177 (Jingle RAW UDP) The class also declares attributes and elements that would be needed during ICE Negotiations.
ContentElementType
          This class models the Content Element of a Jingle element based from XEP-0166
DescriptionElementType
          This class models a Description element as described in the XEP-0167
PayloadElementType
          This class models the PayloadElementType from the XEP-0166
ReasonElementType
          This class models the Reason Element of a Jingle element based from XEP-0166
TransportElementType
          This class models the Transport Element which is contained in a Description element
 

Classes in com.cornell.opencomm.jingleimpl used by com.cornell.opencomm.jingleimpl.sessionmgmt
JingleIQPacket
          This class models a Jingle Element as defined by XEP-0166 This class is based on the earlier Jingle code being used by the network team and is an attempt to make it more general.
ReasonElementType
          This class models the Reason Element of a Jingle element based from XEP-0166
